    • Constructor Detail

      • Product

        public Product(java.lang.String name,
               double naturePercent,
               java.lang.String handcraft,
               int intType)

        Product

        Description: Initializes and creates an instance of a Product with the specified parameters. The constructor sets the attributes of the Product object using the provided parameters.

        Preconditions:

        • name must be a non-null String.
        • naturePercent must be a double.
        • handcraft must be a String.
        • intType must be an int between 1 and 2.

        Postconditions:

        • An instance of a Product is created with all the specified parameters set.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the product.
        naturePercent - The percentage of natural ingredients in the product.
        handcraft - The handcraft information related to the product.
        intType - The type of the product.

    • Method Detail

      • getProductTypes

        public static java.lang.String[] getProductTypes()

        getProductTypes

        Description: Extracts the array from ProductType holding every description associated with a ProductType literal and returns it. The method passes on the descriptios done by ProductType.getProductTypes().

        Preconditions:

        • getProductTypes method in ProductType must be in place.

        Postconditions:

        • A String array is returned holding the descriptions of every Literal.
        Returns:
        A string[] holding all the descriptions representing the ProductType literals.
